This is definitely a place I will patronize again and recommend to others.

The female at the register not only ignored me for at least 10 mins while I waited directly in front of her but also did not acknowledge me before she walked to the kitchen area. Once the female returned she again ignored me and paced back and forth with phone in hand. While waiting for my order, I noticed the female who had been handing the register and phone suddenly start touching and helping to prepare the food without washing her hands or wearing gloves. “How disgusting!” I thought to myself as I kept an eye on my food to make sure she did not have any part in touching or preparing it. When she once again went to the kitchen I mentioned it to the young man and he agreed she should’ve been wearing gloves like everyone else on staff. However, the female came back and not only refused to wear gloves but cursed at the young man in a playful manor and ignored the request. She then looked at me with a few take out plates in her hand and asked what I ordered, as if she would be the one preparing my food to go. I looked at her and confirmed my order then said “I do not like anyone touching my food or anything my food has to go in without gloves on”. She responded with an attitude “I asked you a question. I’m not preparing your food.” I responded “Good. I was just letting you know in case.” FOOD PREP 101 ALL EMPLOYEES HANDLING FOOD SHOULD BE WEARING GLOVES!!! Not to mention her hands and nails were black with dirt and disgusting along with her entire appearance, shirt and all. I’m really disappointed that this will result in me never entering this restaurant while she is there.  Kudos to the rest of the staff😉👍 Thank you guys for remaining professional & friendly during my visits.
